    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Heathrow was founded in 1985 by Italian‑American entrepreneur Jeno Paulucci, who also created Chun King foods.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heathrow%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The community was designed as a British‑inspired enclave, modeled after London’s Heathrow Airport, to evoke gentry and luxury on 2,000 acres of former celery farmland.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Heathrow,_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Heathrow is a master‑planned, gated residential community with roughly 2,200 homes and a private business center.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heathrow%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The American Automobile Association’s national headquarters sits in Heathrow, making it a key hub for travelers nationwide.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heathrow%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Before becoming a suburb, the area produced celery that fed Jeno Paulucci’s Chun King Chinese‑style food empire.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heathrow%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Heathrow lies on the I‑4 corridor, about 19 miles northeast of Orlando, placing it within the Orlando‑Kissimmee‑Sanford metro area.",
